The paper discusses deep learning in spiking neural networks, which falls under the category of neural networks and machine learning. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses supervised and unsupervised learning methods, which are common in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper focuses on computer vision, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Finally, the paper discusses the potential for low-power, neuromorphic hardware, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
